  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "3294750c-f3ba-8003-b5e2-d64643b7a5f8",
      "heading": "Abstract",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Goal-based personalized sequential recommendation; LSTM/RNN grade-prediction model with backprop-based time-slice imputation; compared against exhaustive enumeration",
          "Courses to take next for preparation toward a target course; objective is to maximize probability of earning ≥ B in the target course while recommending a course the student can pass",
          "164,196 anonymized undergraduates; evaluation uses students with at least 2 semesters before Spring 2016",
          "10,430 courses; 4.8M enrollments",
          "UC Berkeley enrollment and grade histories, Fall 2008–Spring 2017",
          "Stage 1: collective training of the course-grade prediction model (Model 2 from prior work). Stage 2: fix model parameters, infer learner hidden state, initialize candidate-course vector with s = (1,0)^n and all-ones weights, then optimize recommendation weights via backprop; enumeration used as baseline",
          "Recommendations are recomputed per learner and per goal after reading the learner’s history; no explicit periodic retraining schedule reported",
          "Semester input = multi-hot co-enrollment vector + grade encoding collapsed to ≥B / <B. Domain filters remove courses already passed and courses above the target course level",
          "Top-10 courses",
          "RNN+Enumeration: high-perf. students 57.65, gap 21.21, overall 49.60. RNN+Backprop: high-perf. students 77.17, gap 6.51, overall 75.78",
          "Main contribution is replacing exhaustive candidate enumeration with per-learner backprop over the recommendation time slice. Backprop improves overall course recommendation accuracy, but reduces separation between high- and low-performance groups",
          "Paper notes: candidate recommendations are optimized independently rather than under a constrained simultaneous-input setting; multi-time-slice imputation is difficult; domain knowledge filters are needed to avoid spurious recommendations; cold start gives generic rather than personalized recommendations"
        ],
        [
          "MOOC",
          "E-Learning",
          "Goal-based personalized sequential recommendation; LSTM/RNN correctness-prediction model with backprop-based time-slice imputation; compared against exhaustive enumeration",
          "Pages/videos to view next in preparation for an upcoming quiz; objective is to maximize predicted correctness on the target quiz",
          "4,763 learners with at least one problem answer",
          "1 edX Physics course; 868 book/video pages plus quiz problems",
          "1,869,406 learner actions: page/video views and problem attempts; 177,623 correct and 104,711 incorrect answers",
          "Stage 1: collective training of problem-correctness prediction model on action sequences. Stage 2: fix model parameters, infer learner hidden state, initialize candidate-page vector with s = (1,0)^n and all-ones weights, then optimize via backprop toward an all-correct target quiz; enumeration used as baseline",
          "Recommendations are generated per learner at a time slice before the target quiz; no explicit online retraining schedule reported",
          "One-hot action per time slice: either page/video view or problem answer. Masked cross-entropy is applied only on answered problems. Filters remove quiz pages and pages that occur after the target quiz",
          "Top-10 pages/resources",
          "Prediction task: accuracy 77.17%, AUC 0.8749; raw correct-answer rate 62.91%. Recommendation eval — RNN+Enumeration: quiz-correct rec. group 72.12, gap 8.10, overall 11.04. RNN+Backprop: 66.51, gap 1.05, overall 12.17",
          "Extends the same goal-based framework from course preparation to within-course MOOC resource recommendation. Backprop gives slightly higher overall overlap accuracy, but much weaker discrimination between better and worse quiz outcomes than enumeration",
          "Same paper-level limitations: independently optimized candidates, difficulty with multi-time-slice imputation, reliance on domain filters, and weak personalization for cold-start learners"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
